<methods>
<methodStep>
<description>
<section>
<title>Experimental Design</title>
<para>Measurements were made annually on three frost lines within burned, unburned and fireline areas. Annual measurements are done in late September as close as possible to maximum thaw depth. The undisturbed community is an open black spruce forest underlain by permafrost.</para>
</section>
<section>
<title>Methods</title>
<para>Three, 20m frost probe lines were set up in the burned forest, perpendicular to the fireline and in the adjacent unburned forest. Ten permanent probe sites were installed using fiberglass poles at 2m intervals. Thaw depth is measured in cm using a graduated frost probe. Measurements are done in mid to late September as close as possible to maximum thaw depth. In some years the fireline probe line is extended on either end. The deeper depths require 2 or 3 operators to reach the frost line.</para>
</section>
</description>
